snippet.title: I Went to FFMIC and Total Gaming Became CS Champion üèÜüî• Live Reaction üò≥
snippet.description:
Today, I witnessed one of the best comebacks in Free Fire history! After four years, the Free Fire India Max Cup returned, and Total Gaming pulled off an epic BOOYAH! In the finals against GodL, GodL had a 2-point lead in the best-of-five series. But Total Gaming made an incredible comeback, leveling the score 2-2. In the final match, with the score tied 5-5, Total Gaming clinched the victory in the last round. It was truly an epic comeback and one of the greatest moments in Free Fire‚Äôs history!

A big shoutout and congratulations to Ajju Bhai, Total Gaming, Fauji ajay mafia and Delete & all for their outstanding performance! Also, kudos to Jonty Gaming and NG Pros for their amazing gameplay. And let‚Äôs not forget Marco from the GodL team, whose sniping was absolutely top notch!

All the best to everyone in the battle royale matches today

snippet.title: Nepathya - Bidai | ‡§¨‡§ø‡§¶‡§æ‡§á
snippet.description:
'While staying at my Goth, looking towards a gloomy sky, I was thinking about the recently lost lives during the Gen Z movement. I believe this was a preventable loss. Words and melody started to play around, motivating me to write and compose.  As I drafted a line, I remembered a song we had made and recorded in 2006 after the tragic Ghunsa Helicopter crash in memory of the stalwarts of conservation and the 24 souls that were victims of the ill-fated chopper. I revisited the song and felt it contained similar feelings I am undergoing at present." 
Amrit had sent this note along with a 4-minute uncut vertical shot he took from his mobile, facing the gloomy sky, to the digital media team at Nepalaya. They thought it would be best to present it in a raw and simple version of a lyrical video with the gloomy sky in the background, filmed by Amrit. 
The song was written by Poet Sarubhakta in 2006 at the request of Amrit Gurung. Amrit had tuned it immediately when the feeling of loss still haunted. 
It was recorded for Nepathya's  9th Album, Aina Jhyal, released in 2010. For some reason, this song was not included.
Bidai is being released after 19 years of creation as a single.

localized.title: Nepathya - Bidai | ‡§¨‡§ø‡§¶‡§æ‡§á
localized.description:
'While staying at my Goth, looking towards a gloomy sky, I was thinking about the recently lost lives during the Gen Z movement. I believe this was a preventable loss. Words and melody started to play around, motivating me to write and compose.  As I drafted a line, I remembered a song we had made and recorded in 2006 after the tragic Ghunsa Helicopter crash in memory of the stalwarts of conservation and the 24 souls that were victims of the ill-fated chopper. I revisited the song and felt it contained similar feelings I am undergoing at present." 
Amrit had sent this note along with a 4-minute uncut vertical shot he took from his mobile, facing the gloomy sky, to the digital media team at Nepalaya. They thought it would be best to present it in a raw and simple version of a lyrical video with the gloomy sky in the background, filmed by Amrit. 
The song was written by Poet Sarubhakta in 2006 at the request of Amrit Gurung. Amrit had tuned it immediately when the feeling of loss still haunted. 
It was recorded for Nepathya's  9th Album, Aina Jhyal, released in 2010. For some reason, this song was not included.
Bidai is being released after 19 years of creation as a single.

snippet.title: Sushant Ghimire - Chitthi (the last letter) | Prod. AVSHK | Official Release | Nahunu ae nirasha
snippet.description:
Wanted to express some words on behalf of those braves who lost their lives in Genz protest. Wherever they are , they might miss home , miss their friends/family , miss everything about being alive . Hope they rest in peace and justice be prevail.

 Chitthi- The last letter ,is a tribute to all of them .

Composed/ Written and Performed by : Sushant Ghimire
Audio Produced by : AVSHK
Mix/Mastered : AVSHK
Recorded at : Esther's Production
Bass Guitar: Dura Himself
Sarod: Sushant Ghimire
Alaap: Rupesh Jha
Back vox: Kaizen , Dura, Rupesh, Sushant.
Artwork : Praeev Shrestha/ Anmol Adhikari

Special Thanks: 
Rijan Maharjan, Bhisma Raj Ghimire.

Lyrics:
Awaz mera gunjiyeki, mai taadhi jaana le
Ki barsau ka yaad ti birsinchau ki, mai chaadi jana le
Chamki rahula ma tara jhai timra
Sparsha chann mera tyahi wari pari
Timro angalo Jhai nyano navayepani
Herirahula ma chamkine gari.... Ma chamkine gari

Baat thiye saatha haru khaasa
feri vetaula katai.....
Aaja nahula kohi majha
Tara mann ma chau sabai
Nahunu ae nirasha....
Ma jaldaigaye ni aaja
yi mera praan saas maa
aago dandani huda ni
siir uthaunu ruda ni

Diyo jhai timi ujyaalo charera
baa aama roye ni afno sahara jalera
thulo manche bannu hai vanthye
timi amar vayeu ni niswartha ladai ladera
feri yo bajrapath kasaima naparos hai
kasaiko sahara aago ma dadaunu naparos hai
eutai binti ki sunchau saba?
kathghara ma nyaya paincha ki aba?

Nahunu ae nirasha....
Ma jaldaigaye ni aaja
yi mera praan saas maa
aago dandani huda ni
Nahunu ae nirasha....
Ma jaldaigaye ni aaja
yi mera praan saas maa
aago dandani huda ni
siir uthaunu ruda ni

Awaz mera gunjiye ki
mai mari jana le.......


¬©Sushant Ghimire 2025

Unauthorized  replication of any content related to this video is not allowed üö´

#sushantghimire #chitthi #atribute
